<TITLE> Cable cut cripples international telelinks for 8 hours </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 31 (bdnews24.com)  International telecommunications were disrupted for over eight hours, from 11:30 pm Sunday to 7:45 am Monday, due to a cut in the submarine cable optical fibre link in Comilla, BTTB said Monday. The cable was cut at Basantpur, some 23 kilometres from Feni, disrupting international telephone calls as well as internet connections, Bangladesh Telegraph and Telephone Board said in a statement. bd
